# Final Validation Phase — E2E Logic & Usability Tests

System context: ~50 internal students, low load. Focus: **logical correctness and working UI behavior only**.

## Gap Analysis

| Flow | Existing E2E | Gap |
|------|------------|-----|
| Registration → OTP | None | Multi-step form interaction, validation, OTP UI |
| Admin fee creation | Page-load smoke only | Form submit, duplicate guard, invalid input |
| Payment recording | Page-load smoke only | Status transition (unpaid → partial → paid) |
| Attendance mark + lock | Page-load smoke only | Mark, lock toggle, locked-edit rejection |
| Input validation | None | Negative numbers, empty fields, double-click |
| Error messages | None | User-facing error visibility on failure |

## Proposed Changes

### E2E Tests (Playwright)

> [!NOTE]
> All E2E tests require the dev server running (`npm run dev`) with a seeded database. They use existing auth fixtures for admin/student sessions.

---

#### [NEW] [register-flow.spec.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/e2e/auth/register-flow.spec.ts)
- **Step 1 validation**: Submit with empty fields → error message visible
- **Step progression**: Fill all fields → advances to step 2
- **Step 2 validation**: Empty academic fields → blocked
- **OTP UI renders**: After registration, OTP input boxes appear
- **Navigability**: "Login" link navigates to `/login`

---

#### [NEW] [fee-management.spec.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/e2e/admin/fee-management.spec.ts)
Uses `adminTest` fixture.
- **Page loads with data or empty state**: No blank screen
- **Create fee record modal**: Add button opens form/modal
- **Empty form submit blocked**: Required fields show validation
- **Negative price rejected**: Numeric guard on base price
- **Payment modal opens**: Click pay on a record → modal appears
- **Zero/negative payment blocked**: Amount field validation

---

#### [NEW] [attendance-flow.spec.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/e2e/admin/attendance-flow.spec.ts)
Uses `adminTest` fixture.
- **Page loads**: Attendance page renders without crash
- **Date picker and filters render**: Subject/batch selectors visible
- **No crash on empty state**: No students for date → shows message, not error

---

#### [NEW] [input-validation.spec.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/e2e/validation/input-validation.spec.ts)
Uses `adminTest` fixture.
- **Expense form**: Empty required fields → submit blocked
- **Expense form**: Amount ≤ 0 → validation error visible
- **Salary form**: Deduction > base amount → error
- **Double-click protection**: Submit button disabled after first click (via button disabled state or loading indicator)
- **Error messages**: All form errors use visible user-facing text (not console-only)

## Verification Plan

```bash
# Run only new validation tests
npx playwright test tests/e2e/auth/register-flow.spec.ts --project=chromium
npx playwright test tests/e2e/admin/fee-management.spec.ts --project=chromium
npx playwright test tests/e2e/admin/attendance-flow.spec.ts --project=chromium
npx playwright test tests/e2e/validation/input-validation.spec.ts --project=chromium

# Run all E2E tests
npx playwright test --project=chromium
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These tests interact with real UI. They require `npm run dev` running with a MongoDB database. Auth fixtures (`adminTest`, `studentTest`) need valid session state files in `.auth/`.
